<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Test Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #1a1a1a;
            color: white;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 40px 20px;
        }
        .button {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 15px 30px;
            background: linear-gradient(45deg, #3b82f6, #9333ea);
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 10px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .button:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 3rem;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Simple Test Page</h1>
        <p>This is a simple test page to check if CSS and content display correctly.</p>
        
        <div>
            <a href="/contact" class="button">Contact Button Test</a>
            <a href="/about" class="button">About Button Test</a>
            <a href="/" class="button">Home Button Test</a>
        </div>
        
        <h2>Test Content</h2>
        <p>If you can see this content properly, then the basic rendering works.</p>
        <p>If buttons are fully visible and clickable, then the z-index issues are resolved.</p>
        
        <div style="background: #333; padding: 20px; margin: 20px 0; border-radius: 8px;">
            <h3>Test Box</h3>
            <p>This box should be fully visible with proper background and text.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
